Author: Nalin Arora [aut],
    Himel Mallick [aut, cre, cph] (ORCID:
    <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4956-2429>)
Maintainer: Himel Mallick <him4004@med.cornell.edu>
Description: Provides MAE-first tools for generic multi-view mediation analysis. Zentangler estimates exposure-associated mediator paths within each assay view, optionally screens candidate mediators, fits retained mediators jointly using early, intermediate, or late fusion, and ranks candidate mediators using a-path and b-path evidence. The package also includes an experimental k-layer sequential mediation screen based on adjacent mediator-layer correlation screening, plus MultiAssayExperiment simulation utilities for method development.
